The Prague Stock Exchange falls into a negative position against the closing of the business.
After the steep fall in the morning, the Prague Stock Exchange was able to correct the losses.
Transactions with the shares of <0xC4><0x8C>EZ reached almost half of the normal day-to-day business.
At the beginning of Tuesday’s business, the Prague Stock Exchange began to collapse on Monday, when it dropped by another six percentage points.
This time there was a reason for the burglary on Wall Street.
In the Czech Republic, too, the reaction of the market to the outcome of the vote of the American House of Representatives, which had refused to support a stabilisation plan for the financial sector there.
Fall of shares in Asia
A dramatic case experienced on Tuesday the stocks on the stock exchanges in Asia, although the indices were able to offset some of the losses over the course of the day.
The index of the Hang Seng Stock Exchange in Hong Kong lost nearly four percentage points during the business day, but was later able to recover some of the losses, thus reducing the decline to about 2.5 percent.
The index Hang Seng China Enterprises, which observes the movement of Chinese shares on the Hong Kong stock exchange, fell by 3.8 percent, in Shanghai the markets were closed.
Stocks on the Sydney Stock Exchange lost more than five percent, but then reduced losses to 4.3 percent.
The Taiwan Stock Exchange fell by 3.6 percent according to its index.
“The timing for the rescue operation in the U.S. is uncertain and will affect the financial markets worldwide,” said Hong Kong’s chief monetary authority Joseph Yam.
Hong Kong, although it belongs to China, determines its monetary policy itself, i.e. independent of the Chinese central bank.
Interest rates in Hong Kong are at the same level as those in the United States.
According to Australian Prime Minister Kevin Rudd, American lawmakers should return to the negotiating table as soon as possible and adopt the draft to support the financial system.
Otherwise, other countries would also be affected by the burglary.
A Bloodbath of American Stocks
The U.S. House of Representatives on Monday rejected the plan to support the financial system, for which up to $700 billion (nearly 12 trillion K<0xC4><0x8D>) should be spent.
The lawmakers ignored President George Bush’s call to support the plan.
Bush’s view is that the plan would regulate the root causes of the financial crisis and thus help stabilize the entire economy.
The American stocks experienced a bloodbath on Monday, and the main stock indices recorded the largest collapse in more than 20 years.
The Dow Jones Index fell by almost seven percent, a similar collapse it had last recorded in 1987.
The index had already fallen before the vote, but there were hardly any signs that the draft in the House of Representatives would not pass, the index experienced a free fall.
U.S. government to pump $700 billion into banks
The top representatives of the U.S. Congress and the government of President George W. Bush have agreed on a broader form of an agreement on financial aid to the U.S. financial system.
This will be agreed at the beginning of next week.
American lawmakers made a breakthrough in talks about the adoption of a rescue plan in the form of a financial aid to the American financial system in the amount of $700 billion (about 12 trillion kroner).
However, this does not mean a victory yet.
Congressmen have to negotiate some details of the agreement before they are allowed to publish the final version of the law and vote on it.
The plan to support the financial system will be negotiated in the U.S. Congress on Monday.
On Sunday, the Chairman of the Committee on Banking and Financial Services, Barney Frank, told Reuters.
According to the Senate, different figures could probably be voted on the plan at the earliest on Wednesday.
According to economists, a communication that the plan is being adopted should be the first significant psychological factor for a revival of financial markets.
After that, however, there is a "frustration" due to the complicated mechanisms that could also help the markets in practice.
Paulson: The plan must be effective
"We have made significant progress.
We have clarified our different views on what a package to stabilize the market should look like,” said Democrat Nancy Pelosi.
According to her words, there could be a final vote on Sunday.
Representatives of the legislators met with US Treasury Secretary Henry Paulson on Sunday night to give the government fund its final form.
It provides for the purchase of unsaleable mortgage assets by financial companies, which plunge financial firms into heavy losses and jeopardise the stability of the entire system.
“We are on the verge of a definitive agreement on a plan that will work and that must be effective in the market.
You have to continue with the health plan, but I think we're on target," Paulson said.
A signal for Asian business
The global financial crisis is also clearly reflected in the stock markets that are falling sharply.
According to Nevada Democratic Senator Harry Reid, legislators are trying to reach a final agreement before Sunday in Congress.
This is to reassure investors of transactions in Asian financial markets, which are in the first time zone where a congressional decision could affect business on Monday.
However, it is not yet clear when both chambers of the American Congress will vote on the law, nor is there any clarity as to whether the negotiations at the last minute could not yet fail to solve a problem.
The legislators hope that it will be passed in the next few days.
But the law will see some changes.
The total amount intended to assist the system shall be divided into two parts.
The initial $350 billion is expected to be made available as soon as possible, as President George Bush called for.
Congress can, however, block the distribution of the remaining money if it has the impression that the program does not perform its function, at another $100 billion and later the final $350 billion.
Bush Positively Appreciates Progress in Negotiations
The president has a veto right in this decision, but Congress can override his veto.
Despite these changes, however, the basic idea of the program has remained, based on obtaining finance for the purchase of bad mortgage securities, the value of which has fallen, because hundreds of thousands of Americans are no longer able to repay their mortgages.
"We worked everything out.
The House of Representatives should be able to vote on the law on Sunday, then the Senate on Monday," Republican Senator Judd Gregg said.
The American President Bush was also pleased with the progress.
His spokesman Tony Fratto said Bush was satisfied with Saturday’s progress and “appreciates the two-sided effort to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy.”
Limitation of golden parachutes
The chairman of the banking committee of Senate Christopher Dodd, the chief negotiator, said the legislators had agreed on a responsibility for the money program, protecting taxpayers from losses, closing benefits, and a schedule for funding the plan.
The new law is also intended to limit the so-called golden parachutes for directors of companies involved in the programme and to set up a committee to oversee the fund.
This is to be headed by the Ministry of Finance.
“We have worked very hard on this and made great progress towards an agreement that works and is important for the market and for all Americans,” Paulson said.
The plan also expects help for homeowners who have problems repaying their mortgage.
The government should negotiate new installments at mortgages it buys, with the goal of lowering the monthly cost to debtors and allowing them to keep their homes.
Marek: Psychological assistance
The proposed plan is a good idea according to the chief economist of Patria Finance David Marek, but implementation will be very difficult.
“And that’s because you don’t know by what mechanism and at what price the problematic assets are bought up.
This will be crucial to how the financial sector and the government divide the losses among themselves,” Marek told the iHNed.cz server this week.
Whether the plan will be adopted now or early next week is not decisive in Marek’s view.
"It is much more important that Congress members agree to support the plan and that they adopt it as soon as possible.
The psychological significance of the agreement on adoption is the most important thing at this moment,” Marek said.
Duel on knife cutting edge: MP3 player against mobile phones.
