In this respect, music players (especially the simplest ones) are significantly more powerful.
That’s why you should expect cheap phones to not be able to play music for more than a few hours.
If you’re still on the phone from time to time, you’d rather buy a charger for the office – this also applies to more expensive devices.
With MP3 players, you won’t have this problem, even the less good ones will last at least 9 hours of uninterrupted operation at once charging.
There is another problem when you want to play the music on your phone.
Unfortunately, only a small part of the devices have a USB port, and not every mobile phone can be connected directly to a PC without special software.
