The drivers, who can be withdrawn because of the alcohol level, will have to install the ‘Alcolock’.
The authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for alcohol levels, installs this system in his car, which prohibits him from starting the car in the drunk state. If he is alcoholized, then the car does not jump.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is now part of the General Prosecutor's report, according to their data, a pilot project, which will last a year.
The purpose is to resocialize the driver, which is why he gets a course for re-education of traffic behavior.
In addition to the Attorney General’s Office, experience has shown, the Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for Automobile Safety will also participate.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of drivers who were shown more than once due to driving under the influence of alcohol were back in control.
The ‘alcolock’ would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the exhaled air and prevents car start when the driver has taken the alcohol test; or when an alcohol concentration is detected that is higher than allowed.
It costs more than 1 000 euros, the costs are borne by the person who imposes the sanction.
In this context, a study conducted in the U.S. in 2007 showed that vehicles equipped with these devices prevented up to 65% of the rule violations as early as the first year after its introduction.
In Spain, 115 lives are expected to be saved each year.
