Some children talk at night.
I mean not those who wake up and tell us something about what happened the day before, but the children who talk during sleep.
If it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be frightened, but in reality this has no meaning.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Surely, more than one of you was told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in life, for example, during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is no single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Often, relationships with other phenomena are sought in sleep, such as nightmares, panic fear at night, enuresis noctura (bedwetting at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason for that.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be due to very high fiber, stress situations or overexertion.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It may be that one speaks quietly in individual words, whispers, or it may be quite the opposite (screaming, crying, long discussions).
In cases where the expression is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and consult with a specialist to check if there is a problem that causes anxiety and thus arises.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, be it, it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
